ce:section.ce:para:
The powder X-ray diffraction analysis corroborated the formation of GQDs, as seen in Fig. 4
                        . A great number of other peaks are also seen. All those peaks are due the presence of citrate. Citrate was used in the preparation of GO/GQDs and was detected by the PXRD analysis (Table 1
                        ). The GQDs has a broad peak close to 2θ = 25o, that could not be properly seen due the citrate phase, which has two intense peaks in the same region. However, the Raman measurement of the purified sample has confirmed the presence of GQDs.
